66QDockAreaLayoutItem::QDockAreaLayoutItem(const QDockAreaLayoutItem &other)
67 : widgetItem(other.widgetItem), subinfo(nullptr), placeHolderItem(nullptr), pos(other.pos),
68 size(other.size), flags(other.flags)
69{
70 if (other.subinfo != nullptr)
71 subinfo = new QDockAreaLayoutInfo(*other.subinfo);
72 else if (other.placeHolderItem != nullptr)
73 placeHolderItem = new QPlaceHolderItem(*other.placeHolderItem);
74}
75
76QDockAreaLayoutItem::~QDockAreaLayoutItem()
77{
78 delete subinfo;
79 delete placeHolderItem;
80}
81
82bool QDockAreaLayoutItem::skip() const
83{
84 if (placeHolderItem != nullptr)
85 return true;
86
87 if (flags & GapItem)
88 return false;
89
90 if (widgetItem != nullptr)
91 return widgetItem->isEmpty();
92
93 if (subinfo != nullptr) {
94 for (int i = 0; i < subinfo->item_list.size(); ++i) {
95 if (!subinfo->item_list.at(i).skip())
96 return false;
97 }
98 }
99
100 return true;
101}
102
103QSize QDockAreaLayoutItem::minimumSize() const
104{
105 if (widgetItem)
106 return widgetItem->minimumSize().grownBy(m: widgetItem->widget()->contentsMargins());
107 if (subinfo != nullptr)
108 return subinfo->minimumSize();
109 return QSize(0, 0);
110}
111
112QSize QDockAreaLayoutItem::maximumSize() const
113{
114 if (widgetItem)
115 return widgetItem->maximumSize().grownBy(m: widgetItem->widget()->contentsMargins());
116 if (subinfo != nullptr)
117 return subinfo->maximumSize();
118 return QSize(QWIDGETSIZE_MAX, QWIDGETSIZE_MAX);
119}
120
121bool QDockAreaLayoutItem::hasFixedSize(Qt::Orientation o) const
122{
123 return perp(o, size: minimumSize()) == perp(o, size: maximumSize());
124}
125
126bool QDockAreaLayoutItem::expansive(Qt::Orientation o) const
127{
128 if ((flags & GapItem) || placeHolderItem != nullptr)
129 return false;
130 if (widgetItem != nullptr)
131 return ((widgetItem->expandingDirections() & o) == o);
132 if (subinfo != nullptr)
133 return subinfo->expansive(o);
134 return false;
135}
136
137QSize QDockAreaLayoutItem::sizeHint() const
138{
139 if (placeHolderItem != nullptr)
140 return QSize(0, 0);
141 if (widgetItem)
142 return widgetItem->sizeHint().grownBy(m: widgetItem->widget()->contentsMargins());
143 if (subinfo != nullptr)
144 return subinfo->sizeHint();
145 return QSize(-1, -1);
146}
147
148QDockAreaLayoutItem
149 &QDockAreaLayoutItem::operator = (const QDockAreaLayoutItem &other)
150{
151 if (this == &other)
152 return *this;
153
154 widgetItem = other.widgetItem;
155 delete subinfo;
156 if (other.subinfo == nullptr)
157 subinfo = nullptr;
158 else
159 subinfo = new QDockAreaLayoutInfo(*other.subinfo);
160
161 delete placeHolderItem;
162 if (other.placeHolderItem == nullptr)
163 placeHolderItem = nullptr;
164 else
165 placeHolderItem = new QPlaceHolderItem(*other.placeHolderItem);
166
167 pos = other.pos;
168 size = other.size;
169 flags = other.flags;
170
171 return *this;
172}

240QSize QDockAreaLayoutInfo::minimumSize() const
241{
242 if (isEmpty())
243 return QSize(0, 0);
244
245 int a = 0, b = 0;
246 bool first = true;
247 for (int i = 0; i < item_list.size(); ++i) {
248 const QDockAreaLayoutItem &item = item_list.at(i);
249 if (item.skip())
250 continue;
251
252 QSize min_size = item.minimumSize();
253#if QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
254 if (tabbed) {
255 a = qMax(a, b: pick(o, size: min_size));
256 } else
257#endif
258 {
259 if (!first)
260 a += *sep;
261 a += pick(o, size: min_size);
262 }
263 b = qMax(a: b, b: perp(o, size: min_size));
264
265 first = false;
266 }
267
268 QSize result;
269 rpick(o, size&: result) = a;
270 rperp(o, size&: result) = b;
271
272#if QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
273 QSize tbm = tabBarMinimumSize();
274 if (!tbm.isNull()) {
275 switch (tabBarShape) {
276 case QTabBar::RoundedNorth:
277 case QTabBar::RoundedSouth:
278 case QTabBar::TriangularNorth:
279 case QTabBar::TriangularSouth:
280 result.rheight() += tbm.height();
281 result.rwidth() = qMax(a: tbm.width(), b: result.width());
282 break;
283 case QTabBar::RoundedEast:
284 case QTabBar::RoundedWest:
285 case QTabBar::TriangularEast:
286 case QTabBar::TriangularWest:
287 result.rheight() = qMax(a: tbm.height(), b: result.height());
288 result.rwidth() += tbm.width();
289 break;
290 default:
291 break;
292 }
293 }
294#endif // QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
295
296 return result;
297}
298
299QSize QDockAreaLayoutInfo::maximumSize() const
300{
301 if (isEmpty())
302 return QSize(QWIDGETSIZE_MAX, QWIDGETSIZE_MAX);
303
304 int a = 0, b = QWIDGETSIZE_MAX;
305#if QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
306 if (tabbed)
307 a = QWIDGETSIZE_MAX;
308#endif
309
310 int min_perp = 0;
311
312 bool first = true;
313 for (int i = 0; i < item_list.size(); ++i) {
314 const QDockAreaLayoutItem &item = item_list.at(i);
315 if (item.skip())
316 continue;
317
318 QSize max_size = item.maximumSize();
319 min_perp = qMax(a: min_perp, b: perp(o, size: item.minimumSize()));
320
321#if QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
322 if (tabbed) {
323 a = qMin(a, b: pick(o, size: max_size));
324 } else
325#endif
326 {
327 if (!first)
328 a += *sep;
329 a += pick(o, size: max_size);
330 }
331 b = qMin(a: b, b: perp(o, size: max_size));
332
333 a = qMin(a, b: int(QWIDGETSIZE_MAX));
334 b = qMin(a: b, b: int(QWIDGETSIZE_MAX));
335
336 first = false;
337 }
338
339 b = qMax(a: b, b: min_perp);
340
341 QSize result;
342 rpick(o, size&: result) = a;
343 rperp(o, size&: result) = b;
344
345#if QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
346 QSize tbh = tabBarSizeHint();
347 if (!tbh.isNull()) {
348 switch (tabBarShape) {
349 case QTabBar::RoundedNorth:
350 case QTabBar::RoundedSouth:
351 result.rheight() += tbh.height();
352 break;
353 case QTabBar::RoundedEast:
354 case QTabBar::RoundedWest:
355 result.rwidth() += tbh.width();
356 break;
357 default:
358 break;
359 }
360 }
361#endif // QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
362
363 return result;
364}
365
366QSize QDockAreaLayoutInfo::sizeHint() const
367{
368 if (isEmpty())
369 return QSize(0, 0);
370
371 int a = 0, b = 0;
372 int min_perp = 0;
373 int max_perp = QWIDGETSIZE_MAX;
374 const QDockAreaLayoutItem *previous = nullptr;
375 for (int i = 0; i < item_list.size(); ++i) {
376 const QDockAreaLayoutItem &item = item_list.at(i);
377 if (item.skip())
378 continue;
379
380 bool gap = item.flags & QDockAreaLayoutItem::GapItem;
381
382 QSize size_hint = item.sizeHint();
383 min_perp = qMax(a: min_perp, b: perp(o, size: item.minimumSize()));
384 max_perp = qMin(a: max_perp, b: perp(o, size: item.maximumSize()));
385
386#if QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
387 if (tabbed) {
388 a = qMax(a, b: gap ? item.size : pick(o, size: size_hint));
389 } else
390#endif
391 {
392 if (previous && !gap && !(previous->flags & QDockAreaLayoutItem::GapItem)
393 && !previous->hasFixedSize(o)) {
394 a += *sep;
395 }
396 a += gap ? item.size : pick(o, size: size_hint);
397 }
398 b = qMax(a: b, b: perp(o, size: size_hint));
399
400 previous = &item;
401 }
402
403 max_perp = qMax(a: max_perp, b: min_perp);
404 b = qMax(a: b, b: min_perp);
405 b = qMin(a: b, b: max_perp);
406
407 QSize result;
408 rpick(o, size&: result) = a;
409 rperp(o, size&: result) = b;
410
411#if QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
412 if (tabbed) {
413 QSize tbh = tabBarSizeHint();
414 switch (tabBarShape) {
415 case QTabBar::RoundedNorth:
416 case QTabBar::RoundedSouth:
417 case QTabBar::TriangularNorth:
418 case QTabBar::TriangularSouth:
419 result.rheight() += tbh.height();
420 result.rwidth() = qMax(a: tbh.width(), b: result.width());
421 break;
422 case QTabBar::RoundedEast:
423 case QTabBar::RoundedWest:
424 case QTabBar::TriangularEast:
425 case QTabBar::TriangularWest:
426 result.rheight() = qMax(a: tbh.height(), b: result.height());
427 result.rwidth() += tbh.width();
428 break;
429 default:
430 break;
431 }
432 }
433#endif // QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
434
435 return result;
436}

438bool QDockAreaLayoutInfo::expansive(Qt::Orientation o) const
439{
440 for (int i = 0; i < item_list.size(); ++i) {
441 if (item_list.at(i).expansive(o))
442 return true;
443 }
444 return false;
445}
446
447/* QDockAreaLayoutInfo::maximumSize() doesn't return the real max size. For example,
448 if the layout is empty, it returns QWIDGETSIZE_MAX. This is so that empty dock areas
449 don't constrain the size of the QMainWindow, but sometimes we really need to know the
450 maximum size. Also, these functions take into account widgets that want to keep their
451 size (f.ex. when they are hidden and then shown, they should not change size).
452*/
453
454static int realMinSize(const QDockAreaLayoutInfo &info)
455{
456 int result = 0;
457 bool first = true;
458 for (int i = 0; i < info.item_list.size(); ++i) {
459 const QDockAreaLayoutItem &item = info.item_list.at(i);
460 if (item.skip())
461 continue;
462
463 int min = 0;
464 if ((item.flags & QDockAreaLayoutItem::KeepSize) && item.size != -1)
465 min = item.size;
466 else
467 min = pick(o: info.o, size: item.minimumSize());
468
469 if (!first)
470 result += *info.sep;
471 result += min;
472
473 first = false;
474 }
475
476 return result;
477}
478
479static int realMaxSize(const QDockAreaLayoutInfo &info)
480{
481 int result = 0;
482 bool first = true;
483 for (int i = 0; i < info.item_list.size(); ++i) {
484 const QDockAreaLayoutItem &item = info.item_list.at(i);
485 if (item.skip())
486 continue;
487
488 int max = 0;
489 if ((item.flags & QDockAreaLayoutItem::KeepSize) && item.size != -1)
490 max = item.size;
491 else
492 max = pick(o: info.o, size: item.maximumSize());
493
494 if (!first)
495 result += *info.sep;
496 result += max;
497
498 if (result >= QWIDGETSIZE_MAX)
499 return QWIDGETSIZE_MAX;
500
501 first = false;
502 }
503
504 return result;
505}

507void QDockAreaLayoutInfo::fitItems()
508{
509#if QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
510 if (tabbed) {
511 return;
512 }
513#endif
514
515 QList<QLayoutStruct> layout_struct_list(item_list.size() * 2);
516 int j = 0;
517
518 int size = pick(o, size: rect.size());
519 int min_size = realMinSize(info: *this);
520 int max_size = realMaxSize(info: *this);
521 int last_index = -1;
522
523 const QDockAreaLayoutItem *previous = nullptr;
524 for (int i = 0; i < item_list.size(); ++i) {
525 QDockAreaLayoutItem &item = item_list[i];
526 if (item.skip())
527 continue;
528
529 bool gap = item.flags & QDockAreaLayoutItem::GapItem;
530 if (previous && !gap) {
531 if (!(previous->flags & QDockAreaLayoutItem::GapItem)) {
532 QLayoutStruct &ls = layout_struct_list[j++];
533 ls.init();
534 ls.minimumSize = ls.maximumSize = ls.sizeHint = previous->hasFixedSize(o) ? 0 : *sep;
535 ls.empty = false;
536 }
537 }
538
539 if (item.flags & QDockAreaLayoutItem::KeepSize) {
540 // Check if the item can keep its size, without violating size constraints
541 // of other items.
542
543 if (size < min_size) {
544 // There is too little space to keep this widget's size
545 item.flags &= ~QDockAreaLayoutItem::KeepSize;
546 min_size -= item.size;
547 min_size += pick(o, size: item.minimumSize());
548 min_size = qMax(a: 0, b: min_size);
549 } else if (size > max_size) {
550 // There is too much space to keep this widget's size
551 item.flags &= ~QDockAreaLayoutItem::KeepSize;
552 max_size -= item.size;
553 max_size += pick(o, size: item.maximumSize());
554 max_size = qMin<int>(QWIDGETSIZE_MAX, b: max_size);
555 }
556 }
557
558 last_index = j;
559 QLayoutStruct &ls = layout_struct_list[j++];
560 ls.init();
561 ls.empty = false;
562 if (item.flags & QDockAreaLayoutItem::KeepSize) {
563 ls.minimumSize = ls.maximumSize = ls.sizeHint = item.size;
564 ls.expansive = false;
565 ls.stretch = 0;
566 } else {
567 ls.maximumSize = pick(o, size: item.maximumSize());
568 ls.expansive = item.expansive(o);
569 ls.minimumSize = pick(o, size: item.minimumSize());
570 ls.sizeHint = item.size == -1 ? pick(o, size: item.sizeHint()) : item.size;
571 ls.stretch = ls.expansive ? ls.sizeHint : 0;
572 }
573
574 item.flags &= ~QDockAreaLayoutItem::KeepSize;
575 previous = &item;
576 }
577 layout_struct_list.resize(size: j);
578
579 // If there is more space than the widgets can take (due to maximum size constraints),
580 // we detect it here and stretch the last widget to take up the rest of the space.
581 if (size > max_size && last_index != -1) {
582 layout_struct_list[last_index].maximumSize = QWIDGETSIZE_MAX;
583 layout_struct_list[last_index].expansive = true;
584 }
585
586 qGeomCalc(chain&: layout_struct_list, start: 0, count: j, pos: pick(o, pos: rect.topLeft()), space: size, spacer: 0);
587
588 j = 0;
589 bool prev_gap = false;
590 bool first = true;
591 for (int i = 0; i < item_list.size(); ++i) {
592 QDockAreaLayoutItem &item = item_list[i];
593 if (item.skip())
594 continue;
595
596 bool gap = item.flags & QDockAreaLayoutItem::GapItem;
597 if (!first && !gap && !prev_gap)
598 ++j;
599
600 const QLayoutStruct &ls = layout_struct_list.at(i: j++);
601 item.size = ls.size;
602 item.pos = ls.pos;
603
604 if (item.subinfo != nullptr) {
605 item.subinfo->rect = itemRect(index: i);
606 item.subinfo->fitItems();
607 }
608
609 prev_gap = gap;
610 first = false;
611 }
612}

614static QInternal::DockPosition dockPosHelper(const QRect &rect, const QPoint &_pos,
615 Qt::Orientation o,
616 bool nestingEnabled,
617 QDockAreaLayoutInfo::TabMode tabMode)
618{
619 if (tabMode == QDockAreaLayoutInfo::ForceTabs)
620 return QInternal::DockCount;
621
622 QPoint pos = _pos - rect.topLeft();
623
624 int x = pos.x();
625 int y = pos.y();
626 int w = rect.width();
627 int h = rect.height();
628
629 if (tabMode != QDockAreaLayoutInfo::NoTabs) {
630 // is it in the center?
631 if (nestingEnabled) {
632 /* 2/3
633 +--------------+
634 | |
635 | CCCCCCCC |
636 2/3 | CCCCCCCC |
637 | CCCCCCCC |
638 | |
639 +--------------+ */
640
641 QRect center(w/6, h/6, 2*w/3, 2*h/3);
642 if (center.contains(p: pos))
643 return QInternal::DockCount;
644 } else if (o == Qt::Horizontal) {
645 /* 2/3
646 +--------------+
647 | CCCCCCCC |
648 | CCCCCCCC |
649 | CCCCCCCC |
650 | CCCCCCCC |
651 | CCCCCCCC |
652 +--------------+ */
653
654 if (x > w/6 && x < w*5/6)
655 return QInternal::DockCount;
656 } else {
657 /*
658 +--------------+
659 | |
660 2/3 |CCCCCCCCCCCCCC|
661 |CCCCCCCCCCCCCC|
662 | |
663 +--------------+ */
664 if (y > h/6 && y < 5*h/6)
665 return QInternal::DockCount;
666 }
667 }
668
669 // not in the center. which edge?
670 if (nestingEnabled) {
671 if (o == Qt::Horizontal) {
672 /* 1/3 1/3 1/3
673 +------------+ (we've already ruled out the center)
674 |LLLLTTTTRRRR|
675 |LLLLTTTTRRRR|
676 |LLLLBBBBRRRR|
677 |LLLLBBBBRRRR|
678 +------------+ */
679
680 if (x < w/3)
681 return QInternal::LeftDock;
682 if (x > 2*w/3)
683 return QInternal::RightDock;
684 if (y < h/2)
685 return QInternal::TopDock;
686 return QInternal::BottomDock;
687 } else {
688 /* +------------+ (we've already ruled out the center)
689 1/3 |TTTTTTTTTTTT|
690 |LLLLLLRRRRRR|
691 1/3 |LLLLLLRRRRRR|
692 1/3 |BBBBBBBBBBBB|
693 +------------+ */
694
695 if (y < h/3)
696 return QInternal::TopDock;
697 if (y > 2*h/3)
698 return QInternal::BottomDock;
699 if (x < w/2)
700 return QInternal::LeftDock;
701 return QInternal::RightDock;
702 }
703 } else {
704 if (o == Qt::Horizontal) {
705 return x < w/2
706 ? QInternal::LeftDock
707 : QInternal::RightDock;
708 } else {
709 return y < h/2
710 ? QInternal::TopDock
711 : QInternal::BottomDock;
712 }
713 }
714}
715
716QList<int> QDockAreaLayoutInfo::gapIndex(const QPoint& _pos,
717 bool nestingEnabled, TabMode tabMode) const
718{
719 QList<int> result;
720 QRect item_rect;
721 int item_index = 0;
722
723#if QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
724 if (tabbed) {
725 item_rect = tabContentRect();
726 } else
727#endif
728 {
729 int pos = pick(o, pos: _pos);
730
731 int last = -1;
732 for (int i = 0; i < item_list.size(); ++i) {
733 const QDockAreaLayoutItem &item = item_list.at(i);
734 if (item.skip())
735 continue;
736
737 last = i;
738
739 if (item.pos + item.size < pos)
740 continue;
741
742 if (item.subinfo != nullptr
743#if QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
744 && !item.subinfo->tabbed
745#endif
746 ) {
747 result = item.subinfo->gapIndex(_pos, nestingEnabled,
748 tabMode);
749 result.prepend(t: i);
750 return result;
751 }
752
753 item_rect = itemRect(index: i);
754 item_index = i;
755 break;
756 }
757
758 if (item_rect.isNull()) {
759 result.append(t: last + 1);
760 return result;
761 }
762 }
763
764 Q_ASSERT(!item_rect.isNull());
765
766 QInternal::DockPosition dock_pos
767 = dockPosHelper(rect: item_rect, _pos, o, nestingEnabled, tabMode);
768
769 switch (dock_pos) {
770 case QInternal::LeftDock:
771 if (o == Qt::Horizontal)
772 result << item_index;
773 else
774 result << item_index << 0; // this subinfo doesn't exist yet, but insertGap()
775 // handles this by inserting it
776 break;
777 case QInternal::RightDock:
778 if (o == Qt::Horizontal)
779 result << item_index + 1;
780 else
781 result << item_index << 1;
782 break;
783 case QInternal::TopDock:
784 if (o == Qt::Horizontal)
785 result << item_index << 0;
786 else
787 result << item_index;
788 break;
789 case QInternal::BottomDock:
790 if (o == Qt::Horizontal)
791 result << item_index << 1;
792 else
793 result << item_index + 1;
794 break;
795 case QInternal::DockCount:
796 result << (-item_index - 1) << 0; // negative item_index means "on top of"
797 // -item_index - 1, insertGap()
798 // will insert a tabbed subinfo
799 break;
800 default:
801 break;
802 }
803
804 return result;
805}
806
807static inline int shrink(QLayoutStruct &ls, int delta)
808{
809 if (ls.empty)
810 return 0;
811 int old_size = ls.size;
812 ls.size = qMax(a: ls.size - delta, b: ls.minimumSize);
813 return old_size - ls.size;
814}
815
816static inline int grow(QLayoutStruct &ls, int delta)
817{
818 if (ls.empty)
819 return 0;
820 int old_size = ls.size;
821 ls.size = qMin(a: ls.size + delta, b: ls.maximumSize);
822 return ls.size - old_size;
823}
824
825static int separatorMoveHelper(QList<QLayoutStruct> &list, int index, int delta, int sep)
826{
827 // adjust sizes
828 int pos = -1;
829 for (int i = 0; i < list.size(); ++i) {
830 const QLayoutStruct &ls = list.at(i);
831 if (!ls.empty) {
832 pos = ls.pos;
833 break;
834 }
835 }
836 if (pos == -1)
837 return 0;
838
839 if (delta > 0) {
840 int growlimit = 0;
841 for (int i = 0; i<=index; ++i) {
842 const QLayoutStruct &ls = list.at(i);
843 if (ls.empty)
844 continue;
845 if (ls.maximumSize == QLAYOUTSIZE_MAX) {
846 growlimit = QLAYOUTSIZE_MAX;
847 break;
848 }
849 growlimit += ls.maximumSize - ls.size;
850 }
851 if (delta > growlimit)
852 delta = growlimit;
853
854 int d = 0;
855 for (int i = index + 1; d < delta && i < list.size(); ++i)
856 d += shrink(ls&: list[i], delta: delta - d);
857 delta = d;
858 d = 0;
859 for (int i = index; d < delta && i >= 0; --i)
860 d += grow(ls&: list[i], delta: delta - d);
861 } else if (delta < 0) {
862 int growlimit = 0;
863 for (int i = index + 1; i < list.size(); ++i) {
864 const QLayoutStruct &ls = list.at(i);
865 if (ls.empty)
866 continue;
867 if (ls.maximumSize == QLAYOUTSIZE_MAX) {
868 growlimit = QLAYOUTSIZE_MAX;
869 break;
870 }
871 growlimit += ls.maximumSize - ls.size;
872 }
873 if (-delta > growlimit)
874 delta = -growlimit;
875
876 int d = 0;
877 for (int i = index; d < -delta && i >= 0; --i)
878 d += shrink(ls&: list[i], delta: -delta - d);
879 delta = -d;
880 d = 0;
881 for (int i = index + 1; d < -delta && i < list.size(); ++i)
882 d += grow(ls&: list[i], delta: -delta - d);
883 }
884
885 // adjust positions
886 bool first = true;
887 for (int i = 0; i < list.size(); ++i) {
888 QLayoutStruct &ls = list[i];
889 if (ls.empty) {
890 ls.pos = pos + (first ? 0 : sep);
891 continue;
892 }
893 if (!first)
894 pos += sep;
895 ls.pos = pos;
896 pos += ls.size;
897 first = false;
898 }
899
900 return delta;
901}
902
903int QDockAreaLayoutInfo::separatorMove(int index, int delta)
904{
905#if QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
906 Q_ASSERT(!tabbed);
907#endif
908
909 QList<QLayoutStruct> list(item_list.size());
910 for (int i = 0; i < list.size(); ++i) {
911 const QDockAreaLayoutItem &item = item_list.at(i);
912 QLayoutStruct &ls = list[i];
913 Q_ASSERT(!(item.flags & QDockAreaLayoutItem::GapItem));
914 if (item.skip()) {
915 ls.empty = true;
916 } else {
917 const int separatorSpace = item.hasFixedSize(o) ? 0 : *sep;
918 ls.empty = false;
919 ls.pos = item.pos;
920 ls.size = item.size + separatorSpace;
921 ls.minimumSize = pick(o, size: item.minimumSize()) + separatorSpace;
922 ls.maximumSize = pick(o, size: item.maximumSize()) + separatorSpace;
923
924 }
925 }
926
927 //the separator space has been added to the size, so we pass 0 as a parameter
928 delta = separatorMoveHelper(list, index, delta, sep: 0 /*separator*/);
929
930 for (int i = 0; i < list.size(); ++i) {
931 QDockAreaLayoutItem &item = item_list[i];
932 if (item.skip())
933 continue;
934 QLayoutStruct &ls = list[i];
935 const int separatorSpace = item.hasFixedSize(o) ? 0 : *sep;
936 item.size = ls.size - separatorSpace;
937 item.pos = ls.pos;
938 if (item.subinfo != nullptr) {
939 item.subinfo->rect = itemRect(index: i);
940 item.subinfo->fitItems();
941 }
942 }
943
944 return delta;
945}

947void QDockAreaLayoutInfo::unnest(int index)
948{
949 QDockAreaLayoutItem &item = item_list[index];
950 if (item.subinfo == nullptr)
951 return;
952 if (item.subinfo->item_list.size() > 1)
953 return;
954
955 if (item.subinfo->item_list.size() == 0) {
956 item_list.removeAt(i: index);
957 } else if (item.subinfo->item_list.size() == 1) {
958 QDockAreaLayoutItem &child = item.subinfo->item_list.first();
959 if (child.widgetItem != nullptr) {
960 item.widgetItem = child.widgetItem;
961 delete item.subinfo;
962 item.subinfo = nullptr;
963 } else if (child.subinfo != nullptr) {
964 QDockAreaLayoutInfo *tmp = item.subinfo;
965 item.subinfo = child.subinfo;
966 child.subinfo = nullptr;
967 tmp->item_list.clear();
968 delete tmp;
969 }
970 }

1093bool QDockAreaLayoutInfo::insertGap(const QList<int> &path, QLayoutItem *dockWidgetItem)
1094{
1095 Q_ASSERT(!path.isEmpty());
1096
1097 bool insert_tabbed = false;
1098 int index = path.first();
1099 if (index < 0) {
1100 insert_tabbed = true;
1101 index = -index - 1;
1102 }
1103
1104// dump(qDebug() << "insertGap() before:" << index << tabIndex, *this, QString());
1105
1106 if (path.size() > 1) {
1107 QDockAreaLayoutItem &item = item_list[index];
1108
1109 if (item.subinfo == nullptr
1110#if QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
1111 || (item.subinfo->tabbed && !insert_tabbed)
1112#endif
1113 ) {
1114
1115 // this is not yet a nested layout - make it
1116
1117 QDockAreaLayoutInfo *subinfo = item.subinfo;
1118 QLayoutItem *widgetItem = item.widgetItem;
1119 QPlaceHolderItem *placeHolderItem = item.placeHolderItem;
1120 QRect r = subinfo == nullptr ? widgetItem ? dockedGeometry(widget: widgetItem->widget()) : placeHolderItem->topLevelRect : subinfo->rect;
1121
1122 Qt::Orientation opposite = o == Qt::Horizontal ? Qt::Vertical : Qt::Horizontal;
1123#if !QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
1124 const int tabBarShape = 0;
1125#endif
1126 QDockAreaLayoutInfo *new_info
1127 = new QDockAreaLayoutInfo(sep, dockPos, opposite, tabBarShape, mainWindow);
1128
1129 //item become a new top-level
1130 item.subinfo = new_info;
1131 item.widgetItem = nullptr;
1132 item.placeHolderItem = nullptr;
1133
1134 QDockAreaLayoutItem new_item
1135 = widgetItem == nullptr
1136 ? QDockAreaLayoutItem(subinfo)
1137 : widgetItem ? QDockAreaLayoutItem(widgetItem) : QDockAreaLayoutItem(placeHolderItem);
1138 new_item.size = pick(o: opposite, size: r.size());
1139 new_item.pos = pick(o: opposite, pos: r.topLeft());
1140 new_info->item_list.append(t: new_item);
1141#if QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
1142 if (insert_tabbed) {
1143 new_info->tabbed = true;
1144 }
1145#endif
1146 }
1147
1148 return item.subinfo->insertGap(path: path.mid(pos: 1), dockWidgetItem);
1149 }
1150
1151 // create the gap item
1152 QDockAreaLayoutItem gap_item;
1153 gap_item.flags |= QDockAreaLayoutItem::GapItem;
1154 gap_item.widgetItem = dockWidgetItem; // so minimumSize(), maximumSize() and
1155 // sizeHint() will work
1156#if QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
1157 if (!tabbed)
1158#endif
1159 {
1160 int prev = this->prev(idx: index);
1161 int next = this->next(idx: index - 1);
1162 // find out how much space we have in the layout
1163 int space = 0;
1164 if (isEmpty()) {
1165 // I am an empty dock area, therefore I am a top-level dock area.
1166 switch (dockPos) {
1167 case QInternal::LeftDock:
1168 case QInternal::RightDock:
1169 if (o == Qt::Vertical) {
1170 // the "size" is the height of the dock area (remember we are empty)
1171 space = pick(o: Qt::Vertical, size: rect.size());
1172 } else {
1173 space = pick(o: Qt::Horizontal, size: dockWidgetItem->widget()->size());
1174 }
1175 break;
1176 case QInternal::TopDock:
1177 case QInternal::BottomDock:
1178 default:
1179 if (o == Qt::Horizontal) {
1180 // the "size" is width of the dock area
1181 space = pick(o: Qt::Horizontal, size: rect.size());
1182 } else {
1183 space = pick(o: Qt::Vertical, size: dockWidgetItem->widget()->size());
1184 }
1185 break;
1186 }
1187 } else {
1188 for (int i = 0; i < item_list.size(); ++i) {
1189 const QDockAreaLayoutItem &item = item_list.at(i);
1190 if (item.skip())
1191 continue;
1192 Q_ASSERT_X(!(item.flags & QDockAreaLayoutItem::GapItem),
1193 "QDockAreaLayoutInfo::insertGap", "inserting two gaps after each other");
1194 space += item.size - pick(o, size: item.minimumSize());
1195 qCDebug(lcQpaDockWidgets) << "Item space:" << item.flags << this;
1196 }
1197 }
1198
1199 // find the actual size of the gap
1200 int gap_size = 0;
1201 int sep_size = 0;
1202 if (isEmpty()) {
1203 gap_size = space;
1204 sep_size = 0;
1205 } else {
1206 QRect r = dockedGeometry(widget: dockWidgetItem->widget());
1207 gap_size = pick(o, size: r.size());
1208 if (prev != -1 && !(item_list.at(i: prev).flags & QDockAreaLayoutItem::GapItem))
1209 sep_size += *sep;
1210 if (next != -1 && !(item_list.at(i: next).flags & QDockAreaLayoutItem::GapItem))
1211 sep_size += *sep;
1212 }
1213 if (gap_size + sep_size > space)
1214 gap_size = pick(o, size: gap_item.minimumSize());
1215 gap_item.size = gap_size + sep_size;
1216 }
1217
1218 // finally, insert the gap
1219 item_list.insert(i: index, t: gap_item);
1220 qCDebug(lcQpaDockWidgets) << "Insert gap after:" << index << this;
1221
1222 return true;
1223}

1261QRect QDockAreaLayoutInfo::itemRect(int index, bool isGap) const
1262{
1263 const QDockAreaLayoutItem &item = item_list.at(i: index);
1264
1265 if (item.skip())
1266 return QRect();
1267
1268 if (isGap && !(item.flags & QDockAreaLayoutItem::GapItem))
1269 return QRect();
1270
1271 QRect result;
1272
1273#if QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
1274 if (tabbed) {
1275 if (isGap || tabId(item) == currentTabId())
1276 result = tabContentRect();
1277 } else
1278#endif
1279 {
1280 int pos = item.pos;
1281 int size = item.size;
1282
1283 if (isGap) {
1284 int prev = this->prev(idx: index);
1285 int next = this->next(idx: index);
1286 if (prev != -1 && !(item_list.at(i: prev).flags & QDockAreaLayoutItem::GapItem)) {
1287 pos += *sep;
1288 size -= *sep;
1289 }
1290 if (next != -1 && !(item_list.at(i: next).flags & QDockAreaLayoutItem::GapItem))
1291 size -= *sep;
1292 }
1293
1294 QPoint p;
1295 rpick(o, pos&: p) = pos;
1296 rperp(o, pos&: p) = perp(o, pos: rect.topLeft());
1297 QSize s;
1298 rpick(o, size&: s) = size;
1299 rperp(o, size&: s) = perp(o, size: rect.size());
1300 result = QRect(p, s);
1301 }
1302
1303 return result;
1304}

1352QList<int> QDockAreaLayoutInfo::findSeparator(const QPoint &_pos) const
1353{
1354#if QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
1355 if (tabbed)
1356 return QList<int>();
1357#endif
1358
1359 int pos = pick(o, pos: _pos);
1360
1361 for (int i = 0; i < item_list.size(); ++i) {
1362 const QDockAreaLayoutItem &item = item_list.at(i);
1363 if (item.skip() || (item.flags & QDockAreaLayoutItem::GapItem))
1364 continue;
1365
1366 if (item.pos + item.size > pos) {
1367 if (item.subinfo != nullptr) {
1368 QList<int> result = item.subinfo->findSeparator(_pos);
1369 if (!result.isEmpty()) {
1370 result.prepend(t: i);
1371 return result;
1372 } else {
1373 return QList<int>();
1374 }
1375 }
1376 }
1377
1378 int next = this->next(idx: i);
1379 if (next == -1 || (item_list.at(i: next).flags & QDockAreaLayoutItem::GapItem))
1380 continue;
1381
1382 QRect sepRect = separatorRect(index: i);
1383 if (!sepRect.isNull() && *sep == 1)
1384 sepRect.adjust(dx1: -2, dy1: -2, dx2: 2, dy2: 2);
1385 //we also make sure we don't find a separator that's not there
1386 if (sepRect.contains(p: _pos) && !item.hasFixedSize(o)) {
1387 return QList<int>() << i;
1388 }
1389
1390 }
1391
1392 return QList<int>();
1393}

1458/*! \internal
1459 Applies the layout and returns the activated QDockWidget or nullptr.
1460 */
1461QDockWidget *QDockAreaLayoutInfo::apply(bool animate)
1462{
1463 QWidgetAnimator &widgetAnimator = mainWindowLayout()->widgetAnimator;
1464
1465#if QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
1466 if (tabbed) {
1467 QRect tab_rect;
1468 QSize tbh = tabBarSizeHint();
1469
1470 if (!tbh.isNull()) {
1471 switch (tabBarShape) {
1472 case QTabBar::RoundedNorth:
1473 case QTabBar::TriangularNorth:
1474 tab_rect = QRect(rect.left(), rect.top(), rect.width(), tbh.height());
1475 break;
1476 case QTabBar::RoundedSouth:
1477 case QTabBar::TriangularSouth:
1478 tab_rect = QRect(rect.left(), rect.bottom() - tbh.height() + 1,
1479 rect.width(), tbh.height());
1480 break;
1481 case QTabBar::RoundedEast:
1482 case QTabBar::TriangularEast:
1483 tab_rect = QRect(rect.right() - tbh.width() + 1, rect.top(),
1484 tbh.width(), rect.height());
1485 break;
1486 case QTabBar::RoundedWest:
1487 case QTabBar::TriangularWest:
1488 tab_rect = QRect(rect.left(), rect.top(),
1489 tbh.width(), rect.height());
1490 break;
1491 default:
1492 break;
1493 }
1494 }
1495
1496 widgetAnimator.animate(widget: tabBar, final_geometry: tab_rect, animate);
1497 }
1498#endif // QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
1499
1500 QDockWidget *activated = nullptr;
1501
1502 for (int i = 0; i < item_list.size(); ++i) {
1503 QDockAreaLayoutItem &item = item_list[i];
1504
1505 if (item.flags & QDockAreaLayoutItem::GapItem)
1506 continue;
1507
1508 if (item.subinfo != nullptr) {
1509 item.subinfo->apply(animate);
1510 continue;
1511 }
1512
1513 if (item.skip())
1514 continue;
1515
1516 Q_ASSERT(item.widgetItem);
1517 QRect r = itemRect(index: i);
1518 QWidget *w = item.widgetItem->widget();
1519
1520 QRect geo = w->geometry();
1521 widgetAnimator.animate(widget: w, final_geometry: r, animate);
1522 if (!w->isHidden() && w->window()->isVisible()) {
1523 QDockWidget *dw = qobject_cast<QDockWidget*>(object: w);
1524 if (!r.isValid() && geo.right() >= 0 && geo.bottom() >= 0) {
1525 dw->lower();
1526 emit dw->visibilityChanged(visible: false);
1527 } else if (r.isValid()
1528 && (geo.right() < 0 || geo.bottom() < 0)) {
1529 emit dw->visibilityChanged(visible: true);
1530 activated = dw;
1531 }
1532 }
1533 }
1534#if QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
1535 if (*sep == 1)
1536 updateSeparatorWidgets();
1537#endif // QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
1538
1539 return activated;
1540}

1747void QDockAreaLayoutInfo::saveState(QDataStream &stream) const
1748{
1749#if QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
1750 if (tabbed) {
1751 stream << (uchar) TabMarker;
1752
1753 // write the index in item_list of the widget that's currently on top.
1754 quintptr id = currentTabId();
1755 int index = -1;
1756 for (int i = 0; i < item_list.size(); ++i) {
1757 if (tabId(item: item_list.at(i)) == id) {
1758 index = i;
1759 break;
1760 }
1761 }
1762 stream << index;
1763 } else
1764#endif // QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
1765 {
1766 stream << (uchar) SequenceMarker;
1767 }
1768
1769 stream << (uchar) o << int(item_list.size());
1770
1771 for (int i = 0; i < item_list.size(); ++i) {
1772 const QDockAreaLayoutItem &item = item_list.at(i);
1773 if (item.widgetItem != nullptr) {
1774 stream << (uchar) WidgetMarker;
1775 QWidget *w = item.widgetItem->widget();
1776 QString name = w->objectName();
1777 if (Q_UNLIKELY(name.isEmpty())) {
1778 qWarning(msg: "QMainWindow::saveState(): 'objectName' not set for QDockWidget %p '%ls;",
1779 w, qUtf16Printable(w->windowTitle()));
1780 }
1781 stream << name;
1782
1783 uchar flags = 0;
1784 if (!w->isHidden())
1785 flags |= StateFlagVisible;
1786 if (w->isWindow())
1787 flags |= StateFlagFloating;
1788 stream << flags;
1789
1790 if (w->isWindow()) {
1791 const QRect geometry = w->geometry();
1792 stream << geometry.x() << geometry.y() << geometry.width() << geometry.height();
1793 } else {
1794 stream << item.pos << item.size << pick(o, size: item.minimumSize())
1795 << pick(o, size: item.maximumSize());
1796 }
1797 } else if (item.placeHolderItem != nullptr) {
1798 stream << (uchar) WidgetMarker;
1799 stream << item.placeHolderItem->objectName;
1800 uchar flags = 0;
1801 if (!item.placeHolderItem->hidden)
1802 flags |= StateFlagVisible;
1803 if (item.placeHolderItem->window)
1804 flags |= StateFlagFloating;
1805 stream << flags;
1806 if (item.placeHolderItem->window) {
1807 QRect r = item.placeHolderItem->topLevelRect;
1808 stream << r.x() << r.y() << r.width() << r.height();
1809 } else {
1810 stream << item.pos << item.size << (int)0 << (int)0;
1811 }
1812 } else if (item.subinfo != nullptr) {
1813 stream << (uchar) SequenceMarker << item.pos << item.size << pick(o, size: item.minimumSize()) << pick(o, size: item.maximumSize());
1814 item.subinfo->saveState(stream);
1815 }
1816 }
1817}

1819static Qt::DockWidgetArea toDockWidgetArea(QInternal::DockPosition pos)
1820{
1821 switch (pos) {
1822 case QInternal::LeftDock: return Qt::LeftDockWidgetArea;
1823 case QInternal::RightDock: return Qt::RightDockWidgetArea;
1824 case QInternal::TopDock: return Qt::TopDockWidgetArea;
1825 case QInternal::BottomDock: return Qt::BottomDockWidgetArea;
1826 default: break;
1827 }
1828 return Qt::NoDockWidgetArea;
1829}

1831bool QDockAreaLayoutInfo::restoreState(QDataStream &stream, QList<QDockWidget*> &widgets, bool testing)
1832{
1833 uchar marker;
1834 stream >> marker;
1835 if (marker != TabMarker && marker != SequenceMarker)
1836 return false;
1837
1838#if QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
1839 tabbed = marker == TabMarker;
1840
1841 int index = -1;
1842 if (tabbed)
1843 stream >> index;
1844#endif
1845
1846 uchar orientation;
1847 stream >> orientation;
1848 o = static_cast<Qt::Orientation>(orientation);
1849
1850 int cnt;
1851 stream >> cnt;
1852
1853 for (int i = 0; i < cnt; ++i) {
1854 uchar nextMarker;
1855 stream >> nextMarker;
1856 if (nextMarker == WidgetMarker) {
1857 QString name;
1858 uchar flags;
1859 stream >> name >> flags;
1860 if (name.isEmpty()) {
1861 int dummy;
1862 stream >> dummy >> dummy >> dummy >> dummy;
1863 continue;
1864 }
1865
1866 QDockWidget *widget = nullptr;
1867 for (int j = 0; j < widgets.size(); ++j) {
1868 if (widgets.at(i: j)->objectName() == name) {
1869 widget = widgets.takeAt(i: j);
1870 break;
1871 }
1872 }
1873
1874 if (widget == nullptr) {
1875 QPlaceHolderItem *placeHolder = new QPlaceHolderItem;
1876 QDockAreaLayoutItem item(placeHolder);
1877
1878 placeHolder->objectName = name;
1879 placeHolder->window = flags & StateFlagFloating;
1880 placeHolder->hidden = !(flags & StateFlagVisible);
1881 if (placeHolder->window) {
1882 int x, y, w, h;
1883 stream >> x >> y >> w >> h;
1884 placeHolder->topLevelRect = QRect(x, y, w, h);
1885 } else {
1886 int dummy;
1887 stream >> item.pos >> item.size >> dummy >> dummy;
1888 }
1889 if (item.size != -1)
1890 item.flags |= QDockAreaLayoutItem::KeepSize;
1891 if (!testing)
1892 item_list.append(t: item);
1893 } else {
1894 QDockAreaLayoutItem item(new QDockWidgetItem(widget));
1895 if (flags & StateFlagFloating) {
1896 bool drawer = false;
1897
1898 if (!testing) {
1899 widget->hide();
1900 if (!drawer)
1901 widget->setFloating(true);
1902 }
1903
1904 int x, y, w, h;
1905 stream >> x >> y >> w >> h;
1906
1907 if (!testing)
1908 widget->setGeometry(QDockAreaLayout::constrainedRect(rect: QRect(x, y, w, h), widget));
1909
1910 if (!testing) {
1911 widget->setVisible(flags & StateFlagVisible);
1912 item_list.append(t: item);
1913 }
1914 } else {
1915 int dummy;
1916 stream >> item.pos >> item.size >> dummy >> dummy;
1917 if (!testing) {
1918 item_list.append(t: item);
1919 widget->setFloating(false);
1920 widget->setVisible(flags & StateFlagVisible);
1921 emit widget->dockLocationChanged(area: toDockWidgetArea(pos: dockPos));
1922 }
1923 }
1924 if (testing) {
1925 //was it is not really added to the layout, we need to delete the object here
1926 delete item.widgetItem;
1927 }
1928 }
1929 } else if (nextMarker == SequenceMarker) {
1930 int dummy;
1931#if !QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
1932 const int tabBarShape = 0;
1933#endif
1934 QDockAreaLayoutItem item(new QDockAreaLayoutInfo(sep, dockPos, o,
1935 tabBarShape, mainWindow));
1936 stream >> item.pos >> item.size >> dummy >> dummy;
1937 //we need to make sure the element is in the list so the dock widget can eventually be docked correctly
1938 if (!testing)
1939 item_list.append(t: item);
1940
1941 //here we need to make sure we change the item in the item_list
1942 QDockAreaLayoutItem &lastItem = testing ? item : item_list.last();
1943
1944 if (!lastItem.subinfo->restoreState(stream, widgets, testing))
1945 return false;
1946
1947 } else {
1948 return false;
1949 }
1950 }
1951
1952#if QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
1953 if (!testing && tabbed && index >= 0 && index < item_list.size()) {
1954 updateTabBar();
1955 setCurrentTabId(tabId(item: item_list.at(i: index)));
1956 }
1957 if (!testing && *sep == 1)
1958 updateSeparatorWidgets();
1959#endif
1960
1961 return true;
1962}

1964#if QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
1965void QDockAreaLayoutInfo::updateSeparatorWidgets() const
1966{
1967 if (tabbed) {
1968 separatorWidgets.clear();
1969 return;
1970 }
1971
1972 int j = 0;
1973 for (int i = 0; i < item_list.size(); ++i) {
1974 const QDockAreaLayoutItem &item = item_list.at(i);
1975
1976 if (item.skip())
1977 continue;
1978
1979 int next = this->next(index: i);
1980 if ((item.flags & QDockAreaLayoutItem::GapItem)
1981 || (next != -1 && (item_list.at(i: next).flags & QDockAreaLayoutItem::GapItem)))
1982 continue;
1983
1984 if (item.subinfo) {
1985 item.subinfo->updateSeparatorWidgets();
1986 }
1987
1988 if (next == -1)
1989 break;
1990
1991 QWidget *sepWidget;
1992 if (j < separatorWidgets.size() && separatorWidgets.at(i: j)) {
1993 sepWidget = separatorWidgets.at(i: j);
1994 } else {
1995 sepWidget = mainWindowLayout()->getSeparatorWidget();
1996 separatorWidgets.append(t: sepWidget);
1997 }
1998 j++;
1999
2000 sepWidget->raise();
2001
2002 QRect sepRect = separatorRect(index: i).adjusted(xp1: -2, yp1: -2, xp2: 2, yp2: 2);
2003 sepWidget->setGeometry(sepRect);
2004 sepWidget->setMask( QRegion(separatorRect(index: i).translated( p: - sepRect.topLeft())));
2005 sepWidget->show();
2006 }
2007
2008 for (int k = j; k < separatorWidgets.size(); ++k) {
2009 separatorWidgets[k]->hide();
2010 }
2011 separatorWidgets.resize(size: j);
2012 Q_ASSERT(separatorWidgets.size() == j);
2013}

2015/*! \internal
2016 reparent all the widgets contained in this layout portion to the
2017 specified parent. This is used to reparent dock widgets and tabbars
2018 to the floating window or the main window

2020void QDockAreaLayoutInfo::reparentWidgets(QWidget *parent)
2021{
2022 if (tabBar)
2023 tabBar->setParent(parent);
2024
2025 for (int i = 0; i < item_list.size(); ++i) {
2026 const QDockAreaLayoutItem &item = item_list.at(i);
2027 if (item.flags & QDockAreaLayoutItem::GapItem)
2028 continue;
2029 if (item.subinfo)
2030 item.subinfo->reparentWidgets(parent);
2031 if (item.widgetItem) {
2032 QWidget *w = item.widgetItem->widget();
2033 if (qobject_cast<QDockWidgetGroupWindow *>(object: w))
2034 continue;
2035 if (w->parent() != parent) {

2039 w->show();

2045//returns whether the tabbar is visible or not
2046bool QDockAreaLayoutInfo::updateTabBar() const
2047{
2048 if (!tabbed)
2049 return false;
2050
2051 QDockAreaLayoutInfo *that = const_cast<QDockAreaLayoutInfo*>(this);
2052
2053 if (that->tabBar == nullptr) {
2054 that->tabBar = mainWindowLayout()->getTabBar();
2055 that->tabBar->setShape(static_cast<QTabBar::Shape>(tabBarShape));
2056 that->tabBar->setDrawBase(true);
2057 }
2058
2059 const QSignalBlocker blocker(tabBar);
2060 bool gap = false;
2061
2062 const quintptr oldCurrentId = currentTabId();
2063
2064 int tab_idx = 0;
2065 for (int i = 0; i < item_list.size(); ++i) {
2066 const QDockAreaLayoutItem &item = item_list.at(i);
2067 if (item.skip())
2068 continue;
2069 if (item.flags & QDockAreaLayoutItem::GapItem) {
2070 gap = true;
2071 continue;
2072 }
2073 if (item.widgetItem == nullptr)
2074 continue;
2075
2076 QDockWidget *dw = qobject_cast<QDockWidget*>(object: item.widgetItem->widget());
2077 QString title = dw->d_func()->fixedWindowTitle;
2078 quintptr id = tabId(item);
2079 if (tab_idx == tabBar->count()) {
2080 tabBar->insertTab(index: tab_idx, text: title);
2081#if QT_CONFIG(tooltip)
2082 tabBar->setTabToolTip(index: tab_idx, tip: title);
2083#endif
2084 tabBar->setTabData(index: tab_idx, data: id);
2085 } else if (qvariant_cast<quintptr>(v: tabBar->tabData(index: tab_idx)) != id) {
2086 if (tab_idx + 1 < tabBar->count()
2087 && qvariant_cast<quintptr>(v: tabBar->tabData(index: tab_idx + 1)) == id)
2088 tabBar->removeTab(index: tab_idx);
2089 else {
2090 tabBar->insertTab(index: tab_idx, text: title);
2091#if QT_CONFIG(tooltip)
2092 tabBar->setTabToolTip(index: tab_idx, tip: title);
2093#endif
2094 tabBar->setTabData(index: tab_idx, data: id);
2095 }
2096 }
2097
2098 if (title != tabBar->tabText(index: tab_idx)) {
2099 tabBar->setTabText(index: tab_idx, text: title);
2100#if QT_CONFIG(tooltip)
2101 tabBar->setTabToolTip(index: tab_idx, tip: title);
2102#endif
2103 }
2104
2105 ++tab_idx;
2106 }
2107
2108 while (tab_idx < tabBar->count()) {
2109 tabBar->removeTab(index: tab_idx);
2110 }
2111
2112 if (oldCurrentId > 0 && currentTabId() != oldCurrentId)
2113 that->setCurrentTabId(oldCurrentId);
2114
2115 if (QDockWidgetGroupWindow *dwgw = qobject_cast<QDockWidgetGroupWindow *>(object: tabBar->parent()))
2116 dwgw->adjustFlags();
2117
2118 //returns if the tabbar is visible or not
2119 return ( (gap ? 1 : 0) + tabBar->count()) > 1;
2120}

2365QList<int> QDockAreaLayout::gapIndex(const QPoint &pos, bool disallowTabs) const
2366{
2367 QMainWindow::DockOptions opts = mainWindow->dockOptions();
2368 bool nestingEnabled = opts & QMainWindow::AllowNestedDocks;
2369 QDockAreaLayoutInfo::TabMode tabMode = QDockAreaLayoutInfo::NoTabs;
2370#if QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
2371 if (!disallowTabs) {
2372 if (opts & QMainWindow::AllowTabbedDocks || opts & QMainWindow::VerticalTabs)
2373 tabMode = QDockAreaLayoutInfo::AllowTabs;
2374 if (opts & QMainWindow::ForceTabbedDocks)
2375 tabMode = QDockAreaLayoutInfo::ForceTabs;
2376
2377 if (tabMode == QDockAreaLayoutInfo::ForceTabs)
2378 nestingEnabled = false;
2379 }
2380#endif
2381
2382
2383 for (int i = 0; i < QInternal::DockCount; ++i) {
2384 const QDockAreaLayoutInfo &info = docks[i];
2385
2386 if (!info.isEmpty() && info.rect.contains(p: pos)) {
2387 QList<int> result
2388 = docks[i].gapIndex(pos: pos, nestingEnabled, tabMode);
2389 if (!result.isEmpty())
2390 result.prepend(t: i);
2391 return result;
2392 }
2393 }
2394
2395 for (int i = 0; i < QInternal::DockCount; ++i) {
2396 const QDockAreaLayoutInfo &info = docks[i];
2397
2398 if (info.isEmpty()) {
2399 const QRect r = gapRect(dockPos: static_cast<QInternal::DockPosition>(i));
2400 if (r.contains(p: pos)) {
2401 if (opts & QMainWindow::ForceTabbedDocks && !info.item_list.isEmpty()) {
2402 //in case of ForceTabbedDocks, we pass -1 in order to force the gap to be tabbed
2403 //it mustn't be completely empty otherwise it won't work
2404 return QList<int>() << i << -1 << 0;
2405 } else {
2406 return QList<int>() << i << 0;
2407 }
2408 }
2409 }
2410 }
2411
2412 return QList<int>();

2415QRect QDockAreaLayout::gapRect(QInternal::DockPosition dockPos) const
2416{
2417 Q_ASSERT_X(mainWindow, "QDockAreaLayout::gapRect", "Called without valid mainWindow pointer.");
2418
2419 // Determine gap size depending on MainWindow size (QTBUG-101657)
2420 const QSize gapSize = (mainWindow->size()/2).boundedTo(otherSize: QSize(EmptyDropAreaSize, EmptyDropAreaSize));
2421
2422 // Warn if main window is too small to create proper docks.
2423 // Do not fail because this can be triggered by a user making MainWindow too small
2424 if (mainWindow->height() < (2 * sep)) {
2425 qCWarning(lcQpaDockWidgets,
2426 "QDockAreaLayout::gapRect: Main window height %i is too small. Docking will not be possible.",
2427 mainWindow->height());
2428
2429 }
2430 if (mainWindow->width() < (2 * sep)) {
2431 qCWarning(lcQpaDockWidgets,
2432 "QDockAreaLayout::gapRect: Main window width %i is too small. Docking will not be possible.",
2433 mainWindow->width());
2434 }
2435
2436 // Calculate rectangle of requested dock
2437 switch (dockPos) {
2438 case QInternal::LeftDock:
2439 return QRect(rect.left(), rect.top(), gapSize.width(), rect.height());
2440 case QInternal::RightDock:
2441 return QRect(rect.right() - gapSize.width(), rect.top(), gapSize.width(), rect.height());
2442 case QInternal::TopDock:
2443 return QRect(rect.left(), rect.top(), rect.width(), gapSize.height());
2444 case QInternal::BottomDock:
2445 return QRect(rect.left(), rect.bottom() - gapSize.height(), rect.width(), gapSize.height());
2446 case QInternal::DockCount:
2447 break;
2448 }
2449 return QRect();
2450}

2452QList<int> QDockAreaLayout::findSeparator(const QPoint &pos) const
2453{
2454 QList<int> result;
2455 for (int i = 0; i < QInternal::DockCount; ++i) {
2456 const QDockAreaLayoutInfo &info = docks[i];
2457 if (info.isEmpty())
2458 continue;
2459 QRect rect = separatorRect(index: i);
2460 if (!rect.isNull() && sep == 1)
2461 rect.adjust(dx1: -2, dy1: -2, dx2: 2, dy2: 2);
2462 if (rect.contains(p: pos) && !info.hasFixedSize()) {
2463 result << i;
2464 break;
2465 } else if (info.rect.contains(p: pos)) {
2466 result = docks[i].findSeparator(pos: pos);
2467 if (!result.isEmpty()) {
2468 result.prepend(t: i);
2469 break;
2470 }
2471 }
2472 }
2473
2474 return result;

2905template<typename SizePMF, typename CenterPMF>
2906QSize QDockAreaLayout::size_helper(SizePMF sizeFn, CenterPMF centerFn) const
2907{
2908 int left_sep = 0;
2909 int right_sep = 0;
2910 int top_sep = 0;
2911 int bottom_sep = 0;
2912
2913 if (centralWidgetItem != nullptr) {
2914 left_sep = docks[QInternal::LeftDock].isEmpty() ? 0 : sep;
2915 right_sep = docks[QInternal::RightDock].isEmpty() ? 0 : sep;
2916 top_sep = docks[QInternal::TopDock].isEmpty() ? 0 : sep;
2917 bottom_sep = docks[QInternal::BottomDock].isEmpty() ? 0 : sep;
2918 }
2919
2920 const QSize left = (docks[QInternal::LeftDock].*sizeFn)() + QSize(left_sep, 0);
2921 const QSize right = (docks[QInternal::RightDock].*sizeFn)() + QSize(right_sep, 0);
2922 const QSize top = (docks[QInternal::TopDock].*sizeFn)() + QSize(0, top_sep);
2923 const QSize bottom = (docks[QInternal::BottomDock].*sizeFn)() + QSize(0, bottom_sep);
2924 const QSize center = centralWidgetItem == nullptr
2925 ? QSize(0, 0) : (centralWidgetItem->*centerFn)();
2926
2927 int row1 = top.width();
2928 int row2 = left.width() + center.width() + right.width();
2929 int row3 = bottom.width();
2930 int col1 = left.height();
2931 int col2 = top.height() + center.height() + bottom.height();
2932 int col3 = right.height();
2933
2934 if (corners[Qt::TopLeftCorner] == Qt::LeftDockWidgetArea)
2935 row1 += left.width();
2936 else
2937 col1 += top.height();
2938
2939 if (corners[Qt::TopRightCorner] == Qt::RightDockWidgetArea)
2940 row1 += right.width();
2941 else
2942 col3 += top.height();
2943
2944 if (corners[Qt::BottomLeftCorner] == Qt::LeftDockWidgetArea)
2945 row3 += left.width();
2946 else
2947 col1 += bottom.height();
2948
2949 if (corners[Qt::BottomRightCorner] == Qt::RightDockWidgetArea)
2950 row3 += right.width();
2951 else
2952 col3 += bottom.height();
2953
2954 return QSize(qMax(i1: row1, i2: row2, i3: row3), qMax(i1: col1, i2: col2, i3: col3));
2955}
